## PART II: THE BIBLICAL YEAR — 360 DAYS

### Scripture Defines Its Own Calendar

The Bible does not operate on a 365-day solar year. Scripture defines the prophetic year as **360 days**.

**Proof from the Flood Narrative:**

> *"In the six hundredth year of Noah's life, in the second month, the seventeenth day of the month, the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up..."*
> — **Genesis 7:11 (KJV)**

> *"And the ark rested in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, upon the mountains of Ararat."*
> — **Genesis 8:4 (KJV)**

- **Duration:** 5 months (2nd month, 17th day → 7th month, 17th day)
- **Days:** 150 days (Genesis 7:24, 8:3)
- **Calculation:** 150 days ÷ 5 months = **30 days per month**
- **Annual Total:** 30 days × 12 months = **360 days per year**

**Proof from Revelation:**

> *"...the holy city shall they tread under foot forty and two months. And I will give power unto my two witnesses, and they shall prophesy a thousand two hundred and threescore days..."*
> — **Revelation 11:2-3 (KJV)**

- **42 months = 1,260 days**
- **1,260 ÷ 42 = 30 days per month**
- **30 × 12 = 360 days per year**

**Proof from Daniel:**

> *"...it shall be for a time, times, and an half..."*
> — **Daniel 12:7 (KJV)**

- Time (1) + Times (2) + Half a Time (0.5) = **3.5 years**
- 3.5 years = 42 months = 1,260 days
- **1,260 ÷ 3.5 = 360 days per year**

### Conversion Table

| Biblical Units | Days | Solar Years (365-day) |
|----------------|------|----------------------|
| 1 Prophetic Year | 360 days | 0.986 solar years |
| 42 Months | 1,260 days | 3.45 solar years |
| 7 Years (1 Week) | 2,520 days | 6.9 solar years |
| 490 Years (70 Weeks) | 176,400 days | 483.3 solar years |
| 1,000 Years (1 Day) | 360,000 days | 986 solar years |
| 2,000 Years (2 Days) | 720,000 days | 1,972 solar years |

