## PART VIII: THE PROPHETIC HOUR — 1984 TO 2026

### Scripture Defines the Hour

> *"And the ten horns which thou sawest are ten kings, which have received no kingdom as yet; but receive power as kings **one hour** with the beast."*
> — **Revelation 17:12 (KJV)**

### Calculating the Hour

Using the Biblical definitions:

- **1 Day = 1,000 years** (2 Peter 3:8)
- **1 Day = 24 hours** (Genesis 1:5 — "evening and morning")
- **1 Hour = 1,000 ÷ 24 = 41.666... years**

**The number 666 is embedded in the very mathematics of the beast's allotted time.**

> *"Here is wisdom. Let him that hath understanding **count** the number of the beast: for it is the number of a man; and his number is Six hundred threescore and six."*
> — **Revelation 13:18 (KJV)**

Scripture instructs us to **count** — to calculate. And when we do, the beast's own number brands the duration of his authority.

### The Historical Anchor: 1884

**October 13, 1884** — Pope Leo XIII reportedly received a vision in which the adversary was granted **100 years** of extended authority to test the Church.

- **1884 + 100 years = 1984**

### The Hour Begins: 1984

**April 9, 1984** — The United States and the Vatican established full diplomatic relations. The U.S. Embassy to the Holy See opened.

This event represents:
- The "healing of the deadly wound" (Revelation 13:3)
- The union of the two beasts (Revelation 13:11-12)
- **The Hour begins**

### The Hour Ends: 2026

- **April 9, 1984 + 41.666 years = December 8, 2025** (the .666 completes)
- **April 9, 1984 + 42 years = April 9, 2026** (the full Hour)

**December 8, 2025** — The Feast of the Immaculate Conception. The .666 of the beast's hour expires on a Roman Catholic holy day.

**April 9, 2026** — The Hour completes. 42 years.

### The Beast Reaches for 42 But Gets 41.666...

The beast wants a clean 42 — the number of authority, of generations, of months.

But the math gives him **41.666...** — forever branded with his own number. The decimal repeats infinitely, never resolving, never becoming whole.

**Always 6, never 7. Always falling short. Never complete.**

